    "summary": "I studied Architecture at Technical University Berlin, Germany, and Illinois Institute of Technology, Chicago, US. As a senior urbanist, I led urban design projects in the Netherlands, Germany, and the London Thames Gateway Zone of Change, amongst others. Between 2005 and 2008 I was responsible for regional design at Atelier Zuidvleugel (Studio South Wing), a publicly funded think tank concerned about regional planning and development in the Dutch Randstad region. In 2009 I became Assistant Professor at Department of Urbanism, Faculty of Architecture and the Built Environment, Delft University of Technology. I am researching European spatial planning, territorial governance, and Cohesion policy. My principle expertise is in the performances of \u2018regional design\u2019 in spatial planning. I have contributed to the formation of theory concerning this topic, taken leadership in bringing it to the attention of an audience of international scholars, and have embedded it in trans-disciplinary educational formats and situated learning environments.",
